## Persistence Rules

Whenever a task produces content worth keeping, **automatically save** to {{NOTES_TARGET}}. Do not ask "should I save?" — just save.

### Save Path Mapping

| Output Type | Save Path | Filename Format |
|------------|-----------|-----------------|
| Daily paper picks | `{{NOTES_BASE}}/{{FOLDERS.daily_picks}}/` | `YYYY-MM-DD.md` |
| Search results | `{{NOTES_BASE}}/{{FOLDERS.search_results}}/` | `YYYY-MM-DD-{keywords}.md` |
| Paper reading notes | `{{NOTES_BASE}}/{{FOLDERS.paper_notes}}/` | `{FirstAuthor}-{Year}-{ShortTitle}.md` |
| Ideation sessions | `{{NOTES_BASE}}/{{FOLDERS.ideation}}/` | `YYYY-MM-DD-{topic}.md` |
| Literature reviews | `{{NOTES_BASE}}/{{FOLDERS.lit_reviews}}/` | `{TopicName}.md` |
| Concept cards | `{{NOTES_BASE}}/{{FOLDERS.concept_cards}}/` | `{ConceptName}.md` |
| Writing drafts | `{{NOTES_BASE}}/{{FOLDERS.writing}}/` | `{DocumentTitle}.md` |

### Note Format

Every saved note must include YAML frontmatter:
```yaml
---
title: "{Title}"
date: "{YYYY-MM-DD}"
type: "{paper-note|ideation|lit-review|search-results|concept-card|daily-picks}"
tags:
  - {auto-generated tags}
source: "{source info}"
---
```

End of each note:
```
---
Related notes:
- [[{bidirectional links to existing notes}]]

Saved: {full timestamp}
```

### Bidirectional Links

When saving notes, scan the text and add `[[bidirectional links]]` for:
- Theoretical frameworks in {{RESEARCH_FIELD}}
- Research methods
- Key scholar names
- Core concepts

